[x] make charter/sidecar association survive file moves $the sidecar binds to its charter by path convention (.stem.json beside stem.actions), so a moved or renamed .actions file orphans its sidecar and silently drops the metadata — most dangerously the irreplaceable CalDAV merge bases (source_vevent, scheduled_at_sync, due_date_sync) that cannot be recomputed. the honest posture is not "keep them together" (unenforceable against a hand mv) but "make separation recoverable and loud": re-join by id, heal in the loader, let doctor flag the mess$ !2 +library %2026-07-11T11:42 #019f4f42-a83a-7df6-9937-7fb79d9934ba
    >[x] hydrate acts from a workspace-wide uuid union $DONE 2026-07-10: read_workspace now folds every sidecar under the charter root into one uuid->ActMeta map (collect_sidecar_acts) and hydrates each action against it, so a sidecar orphaned by a move still reaches its actions by uuid. identical in the normal case — an action's uuid lives only in its own sidecar — and self-healing on move. merge_act keeps the sync bases regardless of file order so an empty re-stamp never clobbers a real record. the conventional path is still read only to report a corrupt sidecar$ +library %2026-07-10T00:00 #019f4f42-a83d-70fc-a831-8c811fc46100
    >[x] add the optional charter-id header to .actions files $the durable-resilience layer on top of the uuid heal: an OPTIONAL leading #<uuid> declaring the charter, rendered away by the editor (conceal to the charter title, like #uuid to an icon) so the human never types or sees it. it lets the .actions file announce its own charter even when empty and decouples it from every filename, so doctor can triangulate identity if any of the three files is renamed or lost. it is a REFERENCE not a second declaration — frontmatter, or the header itself when there is no .md, stays authoritative and doctor verifies agreement. touches the three-artifact round-trip so it is real work: tree-sitter-actions grammar.js gets a charter_id node distinguishable from an action by the absent brackets and regenerates the parser; core parse_document surfaces charter_id; the formatter emits it with a round-trip test per Decision 33; a Topiary query formats the line; the LSP conceals the id and projects the title; doctor cross-checks header against frontmatter against sidecar charter.id. sequenced AFTER the heal, never gating it$ +library,cli,nvim %2026-07-11T11:42 #019f4f42-a83d-7a46-a419-c65a0da25d1a
    >[x] record charter.id in the sidecar at charter creation $DONE 2026-07-10: core stamp_charter_id (idempotent, freeze-preserving) records charter.id in the sidecar; add_charter calls it best-effort after creating the .actions file. note: add_charter charters already carry a frontmatter id, so this mainly makes their sidecar self-identifying for the re-join heal — the charters that need the recorded id for identity are the implicit ones, which the backfill owns$ +cli,library %2026-07-10T00:00 #019f4f85-2677-7ab7-ad6c-d72d7577d1e3
    >[x] resolve charter identity from the sidecar, a derived id yields to it $DONE 2026-07-10: loader resolution pass overrides a non-explicit v5-seed id with the sidecar charter.id; frontmatter_has_id_key guards a declared id from being superseded; inert until ids are written; tested both ways. new precedence: explicit frontmatter id wins, else a recorded sidecar charter.id, else the v5 seed$ !1 +library %2026-07-10T00:00 #019f4f85-2677-787f-bf66-8591849b6d38
    >[x] doctor flags a sidecar charter.id that disagrees with its charter $once identity is recorded the one dangerous state is a sidecar charter.id that contradicts the charter's declared id — a hand-edited frontmatter or a mis-joined sidecar. a finding over that conflict, frontmatter authoritative, closes the loop; the transient no-id-yet state is a backfill target not a warning$ +library %2026-07-11T11:42 #019f4f85-2677-7223-99a2-4cd969733a54
    >[x] backfill charter.id for existing charters $the read side is inert until ids exist and every current charter runs on a derived id. a cleanup command stamps charter.id = the charter's current resolved id for any charter lacking one, freezing today's identities so they survive future renames. same freeze-not-remint discipline as restamping created; belongs with the idempotent cleanup lane$ +cli %2026-07-11T11:42 #019f4f85-2677-7978-ac19-0d925fa741e1
